cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.SD, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with analyzing user-contributed content in online communities, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with community dynamics and user expertise, which falls under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper proposes new models based on probabilistic graphical models, which is a common technique in cs.SD (Software Engineering) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
